{"source_key":"sha256-f88bd5c54ac5fbbfc982c6d403b2565f","record_index":678,"record_hash":"sha256:633ffca54f06a27488a37e3e576b5d377a2bf9f91898111804e29640f1164db9","timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:10:12.312Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"status\":{\"[REDACTED:entropy]\":{\"completed\":\"Ran 5 adversarial subagents. No files edited.\\n\\nVerdict: **the doc is good product-wise, but too optimistic about `but-agentlog` as a server API.** The main fix is to make the API/projection boundary much sharper before building.\\n\\nHigh-signal changes to make:\\n\\n1. **Stop saying PR number maps directly to `gitbutler-review:<number>`.**  \\n   Current code can store `gitbutler-review:{review_id}` or `pull-request:{branch_ref}#{pr_number}`. Doc should say: Forge passes PR facts; `but-agentlog` constructs stored target candidates.\\n\\n2. **Make the public read/projection API mandatory.**  \\n   Today `but-agentlog` exports basically CLI-shaped stuff. The real read APIs are `pub(crate)`. “May need API” should become “must add API before Forge renders pages.”\\n\\n3. **Do not let Forge render current `RecordDetail`.**  \\n   It includes `source_record` and `tool_input`. Redacted, yes, but still too raw for public web. Add an allowlisted `AgentTrailPublicProjection`; no `source_record` by default.\\n\\n4. **Create a small read/projection crate now, not later.**  \\n   Current `but-agentlog` pulls a heavy dependency graph: CLI, workspace, legacy metadata, patched `gix`, git-pinned `git-meta-lib`, etc. For Forge, better shape is something like `but-agentlog-read` / `but-agenttrail-core`.\\n\\n5. **Pinned metadata OID is not actually supported yet.**  \\n   Current reads open current materialized GitMeta state by repo path. Doc should require a GitMeta helper/read handle bound to the fetched OID, or isolate generation per OID.\\n\\n6. **Bare/cache repo support needs explicit API language.**  \\n   CLI rejects bare repos. Forge must not use CLI/default branch discovery. New API should accept a server-prepared GitMeta source without requiring a worktree.\\n\\n7. **Ranking belongs in Agent Trail, not `but-agentlog`.**  \\n   `but-agentlog` should dedupe and return match reasons per session/turn. Forge ranks review matches above branch matches.\\n\\n8. **Snapshot identity should not expose raw session/turn keys.**  \\n   Use opaque projection handles or a salted digest. Keep raw keys out of URLs, HTML, analytics, and public snapshot IDs.\\n\\n9. **Cache key should use GitHub repo ID when available.**  \\n   Owner/repo can rename or transfer. Use forge host + GitHub repository ID as durable key; owner/repo is display/alias.\\n\\nNo must-ask questions from me. My recommended doc patch direction is: **Forge owns PR/GitHub/cache/UI; GitMeta helper owns fetch/materialization/OID binding; `but-agentlog-read` owns target construction, verified lookup, match reasons, and public projections.**\"}},\"timed_out\":false}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-24T15:10:12.312Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}